<p>Detroit's cold climate demands HVAC systems specifically designed for extreme temperature variations and extended heating seasons. The most effective systems for Detroit homes include high-efficiency gas furnaces with AFUE ratings of 90% or higher, paired with central air conditioning units featuring SEER ratings of at least 16. Heat pumps are becoming increasingly popular, particularly cold-climate models that maintain efficiency down to -15¬∞F, making them suitable for Detroit's harsh winters.</p>

