<p>Growing neighborhoods like Corktown and Eastern Market attract younger residents interested in sustainable energy solutions, making them prime areas for solar adoption. The ongoing revitalization efforts in areas like Southwest Detroit and Rivertown create opportunities for comprehensive energy retrofits combining solar panels with high-efficiency HVAC systems. Suburban-style neighborhoods on Detroit's outskirts, such as those near the Grosse Pointe border, typically have larger homes with ample roof space, making them ideal for larger solar installations that can support electric vehicle charging and all-electric HVAC systems.</p>

